        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 10:14PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1014 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chivington, or 19 miles north of Lamar, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sheridan Lake, Chivington, Brandon, Towner, Bristol, and Queens
Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
